This paper proposes a method to combine semi-supervised learning with weakly-supervised learning for deep neural networks. The paper focuses on improving the training efficiency and achieving state-of-the-art performance in a specific challenge related to acoustic scene classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SD (Sound), cs.SI (Speech and Signal Processing), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
